24/02/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The influential businessman and independent parliamentarian Trifun Kostovski is likely to be nominated as presidential candidate of the ruling coalition parties SDSM and LDP, <I>Dnevnik</I> reported Monday (23 February), citing party sources. 
According to the daily, Kostovski was chosen because of his high popularity rating in the latest polls. 
He is also likely to receive the approval of the international community.
In other news, Macedonia and Slovenia signed an accord on co-operation in the defence sector Monday. 
In part, it calls for the exchange of experience in preparing for NATO membership. 
(Dnevnik - 24/02/04; MIA, A1 TV - 23/02/04)
